      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's weird when you say it like that. a void. it actually feels true. i look at the clock and i realize i've just been staring at the wall for hours and i don't even care. i don't care about tomorrow or next week. it just feels so heavy, like a weight i can't carry anymore. do you think it's normal to feel like... like there's just no way to ever feel whole again? like the only way to stop the heaviness is to just not be here?",
